main: ^Empanada is a signature food of Ilocos, Norte particularly in Batac. It is derived from a Spanish word meaning to wrap and coat in bread.

c-0: ^It has a crispy thin orange shell and is filled with longganisa, bean sprouts, and egg. The rice flour-based shell is colored using achuete.
^The celebration of this city's famous traditional fast food attracting locals and tourists elsewhere comes with the City Charter Day of Batac every 23rd of June.
